  sodium: 2 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/chorizo-crusted-tilapia-37-578f7660544b1846128b4568
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Fusion
servings: 2
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the @diced chorizo{2%pieces} into even
smaller pieces and mash it with the flat edge of your #knife{}. Heat a splash of
@olive oil{1%splash} in a #frying pan{} over medium-low heat and cook your
chorizo for ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Try not to get too much colour on the chorizo (as you want to do this later
> when it's on the fish).

Add the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g}, mix everything up, then allow it to cool.

Cut the @new potatoes{2} into quarters and then peel &roughly chop the
@onion{2}(peeled and roughly chopped) into 1cm cubes. Toss your potatoes in a
splash of @olive oil{1%splash} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.
Lay out on a #baking tray{} and cook on the top shelf of your oven for
~{10%minutes}.

After ~{10%minutes}, add your onion to the baking tray with your potatoes,
give it all a good shake and cook for another ~{10%minutes}.

> When the potatoes are crispy around the edges they're done.

Pat the fish dry with some #kitchen paper{} and season with a pinch of
@salt{pinch}. Pile your chorizo mix on top of each @tilapia fillet{4} and push
it down with your hands to make a nice crust.

Lightly grease a second baking tray with @olive oil{1%splash} and lay on your
crusted fillets. Move your potatoes down a shelf and cook your fish on the top
shelf of your oven for ~{5%minutes}. Then, turn on your #grill{} to its highest
setting and allow your fish to grill for a further ~{2-3%minutes}, until the
crust is golden and crispy.

> Your potatoes can remain in the oven while your fish grills.

Stir the @wild rocket{2} through your cooked potatoes and onion, test the
seasoning and add more salt if required and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%splash}.

> For extra flavour, pour over any oil from the fish tray that escapes from the
> chorizo crust.

Dish out your potatoes, onion and rocket and top with your chorizo crusted
tilapia.